becomes infectious that's the word then he says further a householder with wealth thus gained the noble disciple makes provision against the losses that might arise in account of fire and floods kings and bandits and unloved heirs remember that one from last time unloved heirs and he makes himself secure against them this is the second case of wealth gone to good use so

